The paper proposes a novel method for rank aggregation, which is a problem commonly studied in computer science. The use of Lehmer codes and subdiagonal images suggests a connection to combinatorics and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the performance of the method in simulations, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of scalar median and mode computations suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the method on partial rankings, which suggests a connection to social and information networks (cs.SI).
